# Sovereign Analyst — Project Context

A personal finance and investment research tool. It tracks an equity portfolio,
calculates performance metrics, and downloads SEC filings for fundamental analysis.

## Architecture

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `core/portfolio_engine.py` | Central engine — all portfolio logic lives here |
| `scripts/fetch_filings.py` | SEC EDGAR downloader — fetches and saves 10-K filings |
| `data/transactions_sample.csv` | Source of truth for all trades and income |
| `data/.price_cache.json` | 15-minute yfinance price cache — never commit this |
| `data/raw_filings/` | Downloaded SEC 10-K text files |

## Absolute Non-Negotiables

- **Never hardcode credentials.** API keys, User Agents, and secrets go in `.env` only.
- **Never use the system Python.** Always run via `.venv` (Python 3.14+).
- **Never bypass ACB.** All cost basis calculations must use the Average Cost Basis method in chronological order. Do not simplify to a plain average.
- **Never skip validation.** Every pipeline run must execute `run_validations()`. Do not remove or comment it out.

## Transaction Types (CSV Contract)

| type | Cash | Quantity | Accounting |
|------|------|----------|------------|
| `buy` | decreases | increases | grows cost basis |
| `sell` | increases | decreases | records realised P/L via ACB |
| `dividend` | increases | unchanged | tracked separately, not in cost basis |
| `income` | increases | N/A | non-investment cash flow |
| `expense` | decreases | N/A | non-investment cash flow |

Quantity is always a positive number. Direction is inferred from the `type` column.
